snippet.textDisplay:
The future is exciting for English cricket. It appears we have finally replaced Strauss and Cook, with Burns and Sibley. Denly and Crawley are good options for three. Pope is an exciting talent for six. Stokes somehow keeps getting even better (just don't give him the curse of captaincy!) It's a refreshing change to see England have decent batting options!

I just hope the selectors don't go back into old habits and start giving has-beens more chances (Bairstow, Roy, Vince, Ali - the list is far too long!) Long may they remain out of the picture. Also, it's about time Ben Foakes got a fair go as keeper. He's already shown his quality, whereas Buttler is very inconsistent with his batting. That is one change I would make now. He deserves a chance.

snippet.textDisplay: Feels like every member of the team contributed to that win. Crawley for his catches and setting the tone in the second innings. Sibley for his outstanding hundred. Denny for his gritty batting and his crucial breakthroughs in the second innings. Root for his fantastic captaincy and flashy half century. Stokes for absolutely everything. Pope for his hard fought 61* in the first innings. Buttler for his wicket keeping and taking some important catches. Curran for his ability to pick up wickets at important times. Bess for dislodging Elgar on 88. Broad for his persistent line and length in the first innings and getting a key wicket in the second innings. Finally, Anderson for his brilliant 5-40 and his spell of reverse swing late on day 4 and early on day 5
snippet.textOriginal: Feels like every member of the team contributed to that win. Crawley for his catches and setting the tone in the second innings. Sibley for his outstanding hundred.
